# Kerberos Basics

## What is Kerberos?

Kerberos is an authentication protocol used by Active Directory.

## Purpose

Allows users to authenticate once and use tickets to access resources without repeatedly sending passwords.

## Benefits

- Reduces password exposure
- Supports Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Improves authentication security

## Key Concept

User
↓
Authenticate
↓
Receive Ticket
↓
Access Resources Using Ticket
